@@ -0,0 +1,120 @@
+boot: Reorganize boot menu keyboard layout to QWERTY order with TPM on m key
+
+Replace the alphabetical menu key layout with QWERTY keyboard order for more
+intuitive key selection. The new layout follows standard keyboard row order:
+numbers (1-0), then QWERTY rows (q-p, a-l, z-n), supporting 35 boot entries
+total. Move TPM menu from t key to m key - the last usable key at the end of
+the last usable keyboard row, to avoid mixing it with the regular menu entries.
+
+Rename menuchars[] to keyboard_keys[] to clarify this array represents physical
+keyboard layout rather than abstract menu characters. This prepares the codebase
+for upcoming numpad support addition with a separate logic for numpad key input.
+
+Signed-off-by: Mike Banon <mikebdp2@gmail.com>
+---
+ src/boot.c | 33 ++++++++++++++++-----------------
+ 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 17 deletions(-)
+
+diff --git a/src/boot.c b/src/boot.c
+index 8ebf5edc..55308865 100644
