+boot: Add advanced numpad input and dual-function Enter key support
+
+Implement full numeric keypad support with distinct modes based on list size.
+For ten or fewer entries, single digits trigger immediate boot, mapping zero to
+the tenth slot. Larger lists enable multi-digit entry (up to 35) with real-time
+visual feedback showing the selected index and corresponding keyboard key hint.
+
+Enhance navigation by allowing rapid scrolling through options using the Numpad
+Plus and Minus keys to increment or decrement the selection number instantly.
+The Enter key adapts dynamically to context, toggling pages when idle or
+confirming the pending numpad selection, while Numpad Star opens the TPM menu.
+
+Refresh the on-screen help text to explicitly advertise slash and backslash as
+menu triggers alongside detailed numpad usage instructions. The display now
+dynamically updates to show page numbers, current selection hints, and clear
+prompts for entering or confirming choices, ensuring users always see exactly
+how to interact with the expanded boot list regardless of device count.
+
+Signed-off-by: Mike Banon <mikebdp2@gmail.com>
